                "citation_count": 3,
                "reference_count": 26,
                "abstract": "AbstractConsider a form g(x1,...,xs) of degree d, having coefficients in the completion \n$$\\mathbb{F}_q ((1/t))$$\n of the field of fractions \n$$\\mathbb{F}_q (t)$$\n associated to the finite field \n$$\\mathbb{F}_q$$\n. We establish that whenever s > d2, then the form g takes arbitrarily small values for non-zero arguments \n$$x \\in \\mathbb{F}_q [t]^s$$\n. We provide related results for problems involving distribution modulo \n$$\\mathbb{F}_q [t]$$\n, and analogous conclusions for quasi-algebraically closed fields in general.",
